title: Density of the population of Finland in 2018 , by region
yAxis: Number of inhabitants per square kilometer
summary: This is a bar chart representing Finnish Region in the x axis and Number of inhabitants per square kilometer in the y axis.
The Number of inhabitants per square kilometer is highest at Finnish Region Uusimaa and lowest at Finnish Region Lapland.
The difference of Number of inhabitants per square kilometer between the highest and lowest Finnish Region is 181.8.
min_summary: This bar chart has 19 columns on the x axis representing Finnish Region, and Number of inhabitants per square kilometer in each Finnish Region on the y axis.
The Number of inhabitants per square kilometer is highest at Finnish Region Uusimaa and lowest at Finnish Region Lapland.
mid_summary: This is a bar chart representing Finnish Region in the x axis and Number of inhabitants per square kilometer in the y axis.
The Number of inhabitants per square kilometer is highest at Finnish Region Uusimaa and lowest at Finnish Region Lapland.
The difference of Number of inhabitants per square kilometer between the highest and lowest Finnish Region is 181.8.
max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Number of inhabitants per square kilometer for 19 number of Finnish Regions.
The maximum Number of inhabitants per square kilometer 183.7 is found at Finnish Region Uusimaa and the minimum is found at Lapland where Finnish Region is 1.9.
There is a difference of 181.8 between the maximum Finnish Region Uusimaa and minimum Finnish Region Lapland.
The Finnish Region Uusimaa has the highest Number of inhabitants per square kilometer, followed by Southwest Finland, and Pirkanmaa. Down to the Finnish Region Lapland which is the lowest.
The Finnish Region Lapland has 6.18 times less Number of inhabitants per square kilometer than average.
The Number of inhabitants per square kilometer is 564.8 if we add up values of all Finnish Regions.
